Results.ReviewText: I bought both 6-7 and 8-9 sizes.  Looks-wise, these are GREAT! Sizing is an issue, though.  While the 6-7 fits my foot to the brink, it is too tight and I know if I wore them for an extended period of time, I would get both sweaty (and therefore, smelly) feet, and worse - sores on top of my feet. 8-9 felt MUCH MORE comfortable, but they are an inch longer than my foot.  In idea, I could comfortably wear 8-9 size, but they're still a bit too loose for my convenience.  I wish they made them in INDIVIDUAL SIZES 6, 7, 8, 9, etc, instead of the more general one-size-fits-all sizes 6-7, 8-9, etc.  I suggest you try them at the store rather than buying online, because sizing might be an issue.
Results.Title: Great sandals, but sizing is an issue!
